        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>The following is a list of the types of alerts that can be created in SF Agent Desktop:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Global</li>
	<li>Business Unit</li>
	<li>Account</li>
	<li>Contact</li>
	<li>Asset</li>
</ul>


<p>These alerts can contain sensitive information that should only be viewed when needed, and only by users who are authorized for the line of business to which the alert is related. For example, an alert that is created that is related to a contact, and the contact is a MLB and IIC contact, the alert should only be viewed by users who are authorized for those business units.</p>

<p>When an alert is <b>created</b> or <b>edited</b>, the Alert Business Unit fields must be populated as follows:</p>

<p>1. Global Alert: When the Alert has IsGlobal__c = True then update ALL Alert Business Unit fields to True:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Alert.IIC__c = True</li>
	<li>Alert.GB__c = True</li>
	<li>Alert.MI__c = True</li>
	<li>Alert.MLB__c = True</li>
	<li>Alert.MMF__c = True</li>
	<li>Alert.MS__c = True</li>
</ul>


<p>2. Business Unit Alert: When the Alert has Contact_Center_BU_<em>c &lt;&gt; null then the Alert Contact_Center_BU</em><em>c field picklist field value must be used to map to the checkbox fields as follows (Contact_Center_BU</em>_c/LOB field):<br/>
IIC = Alert.IIC__c = True<br/>
MI = Alert.MI__c = True<br/>
GB = Alert. GB__c = True<br/>
MMF = Alert.MMF__c = True<br/>
MS = Alert.MS__c = True<br/>
MLB = Alert.MLB__c = True </p>

<p>3. Account Alert: When the Alert has a Related_Account_<em>c &lt;&gt; null then retrieve the related Account record's LOB field assignment (Account.IIC</em><em>c, Account.GB</em><em>c, Account.MI</em><em>c, Account.MLB</em><em>c, Account.MMF</em><em>c, Account.MS</em>_c) and propagate to the LOB fields on the Alert as follows (Account LOB/Alert LOB):<br/>
Account.IIC_<em>c = True then Alert.IIC</em>_c = True<br/>
Account.GB_<em>c = True then Alert.GB</em>_c = True<br/>
Account.MI_<em>c = True then Alert.MI</em>_c = True<br/>
Account.MLB_<em>c = True then Alert.MLB</em>_c = True<br/>
Account.MMF_<em>c = True then Alert.MMF</em>_c = True<br/>
Account.MS_<em>c = True then Alert.MS</em>_c = True</p>

<p>4. Contact Alert: When the Alert has a Related_Contact_<em>c &lt;&gt; null then retrieve the related Contact record's LOB field assignment (Contact.IIC</em><em>c, Contact.GB</em><em>c, Contact.MI</em><em>c, Contact.MLB</em><em>c, Contact.MMF</em><em>c, Contact.MS</em>_c) and propagate to the LOB fields on the Alert as follows (Contact LOB/Alert LOB):<br/>
Contact.IIC_<em>c = True then Alert.IIC</em>_c = True<br/>
Contact.GB_<em>c = True then Alert.GB</em>_c = True<br/>
Contact.MI_<em>c = True then Alert.MI</em>_c = True<br/>
Contact.MLB_<em>c = True then Alert.MLB</em>_c = True<br/>
Contact.MMF_<em>c = True then Alert.MMF</em>_c = True<br/>
Contact.MS_<em>c = True then Alert.MS</em>_c = True</p>

<p>5. Asset Alert: When the Alert has a Related_Asset_<em>c &lt;&gt; null then retrieve the related Asset record's LOB field assignment (Asset.IIC</em><em>c, Asset.GB</em><em>c, Asset.MI</em><em>c, Asset.MLB</em><em>c, Asset.MMF</em><em>c, Asset.MS</em>_c) and propagate to the LOB fields on the Alert as follows (Asset LOB/Alert LOB):<br/>
Asset.IIC_<em>c = True then Alert.IIC</em>_c = True<br/>
Asset.GB_<em>c = True then Alert.GB</em>_c = True<br/>
Asset.MI_<em>c = True then Alert.MI</em>_c = True<br/>
Asset.MLB_<em>c = True then Alert.MLB</em>_c = True<br/>
Asset.MMF_<em>c = True then Alert.MMF</em>_c = True<br/>
Asset.MS_<em>c = True then Alert.MS</em>_c = True</p>


<p>*Important Note: The alert record can only have ONE type of Alert. It can be Global OR Business Unit OR Account OR Contact OR Asset. This is controlled by a custom validation rule Validate_BU_Contact_Asset_Global. Because of this, finding the type of Alert can be done by checking if the fields IsGlobal_<em>c, Contact_Center_BU</em><em>c, Related_Account</em><em>c, Related_Contact</em><em>c, Related_Asset</em>_c are populated.</p>
